<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:%22Senatorial_courtesy%22_-_Gordon_Ross_1911._LCCN2011648906.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/%22Senatorial_courtesy%22_-_Gordon_Ross_1911._LCCN2011648906.jpg/250px-%22Senatorial_courtesy%22_-_Gordon_Ross_1911._LCCN2011648906.jpg" decoding="async" width="250" height="166" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/%22Senatorial_courtesy%22_-_Gordon_Ross_1911._LCCN2011648906.jpg/500px-%22Senatorial_courtesy%22_-_Gordon_Ross_1911._LCCN2011648906.jpg 1.5x" data-file-width="8652" data-file-height="5757" /></a><figcaption>One-third of the world... usurp and greedily waste three-quarters of the world’s food, and some 83 per cent of all other resources [...] the result of <a href="/wiki/Greed" title="Greed">greed</a>, lack of <a href="/wiki/Compassion" title="Compassion">compassion</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Complacency" title="Complacency">complacency</a>.  It is <a href="/wiki/Unfair" class="mw-redirect" title="Unfair">unfair</a> and extraordinarily <a href="/wiki/Dangerous" class="mw-redirect" title="Dangerous">dangerous</a> for the <a href="/wiki/Security" title="Security">security</a> of the <a href="/wiki/World" title="World">world</a>.</figcaption></figure>
